RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DA JOURNEYGIRL led the way throughout, raced in the three path around the turn, swung wide entering the stretch and held her lead to the wire. THE MONEY MACHINE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, began to move up while racing in the three path around the bend and continued to improve position in the lane. MY BATON ROUGE veered in sharply leaving the gate, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and kept on in the stretch. WIFEY MATERIAL raced off the pace on the outside early, navigated the turn from the three path and made no bid. SORTARIA raced off the pace on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, continued around the turn in the two path and was empty in the lane. LUVISANAKI chased the leader up the backstretch, raced in the two path around the bend and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIKING IT TWISTED led the way on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and held that margin to the wire. PONY GIRL bumped mildly with the horse to her inside leaving the gate, recovered to chase the leader up the backstretch, challenged from the four path coming around the bend and kept on to the finish. BARBARA pressed the pace on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, dropped back while saving ground around the turn and finished evenly from there. I'M A CUTIE raced off the pace on the inside early, came around the turn in the two path and gained ground mildly in the stretch while never threatening. BID ONCE bumped with the horses to both sides and was pinched back leaving the gate, recovered to stalk the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid while racing in the three path around the bend and flattened out in the lane. LADY MISTRESS bumped with the horse to her outside at the start, trailed the field throughout, saved ground around the turn and was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 22 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since December 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ TRIUMPHANT angled in to lead the field on the inside up the backstretch, continued to show the way racing in the two path around the turn and held off a closer in late stretch. ASSERT DOMINANCE veered out and bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, was in traffic early and settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid while saving ground around the bend and gained ground late. THAT'S MY BOI TOY stalked the pacesetters between horses through the opening quarter of a mile, navigated the far turn from the three path, began a bid passing the quarter pole and improved position mildly in the stretch. FELIX THE FOX hopped up and was bumped by the horse to his inside at the break, recovered to track the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, came around the turn in the four path and finished evenly. PUNX was bumped and forced to check while having contact with several horses just out of the gate, dropped back to race off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and never threatened. LUIS TWO GUNS chased the leader on the inside through the opening stages, saved ground around the bend and faded in the stretch. DON H drifted in and bumped with the horses to his inside in the opening strides, pressed the pace on the outside up what remained of the backstretch, navigated the turn from the four path and tired in the lane. THE RIDER OF HORSE THREE, PUNX, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE SEVEN, TIZ TRIUMPHANT, CLAIMING INTERFERENCE AT THE START. THE RIDER OF HORSE FOUR, ASSERT DOMINANCE, ALSO CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST HORSE SEVEN, TIZ TRIUMPHANT, AND HORSE SIX, DON H, CITING INTERFERENCE AT THE STATRT. UPON REVIEW, THE STEWARDS MADE NO CHANGES TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GET EVEN raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the pace setter up the backstretch, took over the lead while saving ground headed into the far turn and held clear from there. URBAN BEACH raced at the back of the pack on the outside through the opening half mile, saved ground around the far turn, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and gained ground while drifting out to the wire. TAKEOVER KASH bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack between horses, began a bid racing in the four and five path around the far turn and improved position in the lane. SOUTHERN CIVILITY hopped up leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first bend, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the second turn and finished evenly. THE POINT ROAD raced into traffic and was forced to steady early, saved ground around the first turn, trailed the field up the backstretch, began to move up while racing in the three path around the far turn and continued to gain ground late. LORD OF THE NILE raced off the pace on the inside around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend and gained ground mildly in the lane. SIDNEY'S BID bumped with the horse to her inside at the start, raced in the three path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, navigated the far turn from the four path and faded in the stretch. COLORS led the field while saving ground through the opening half mile, gave way while racing in the three path around the second bend and continued to tire in the lane. CHEVAL DORE raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn still in the two path and was empty in the stretch. OZAH raced in the two path around the first turn, settled at the back of the pack on the inside up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far bend and was never a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 8 1 1/16M Turf CR: 79. Claiming Purse 17100. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 22 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since December 22 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Races Where Entered For $12,500 O r Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Condition Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISTA DONZELLA raced in the three path around the first turn, pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far turn, was bumped by AIDINANDABETTING when that rival forced him into CHINA BEACH near the quarter pole and kicked clear in the lane. CHINA BEACH raced in the two path around the first turn, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the bend, was bumped by MISTA DONZELLA when that rival was forced into his lane and chased the winner home from there. BATTLE CREEK raced in the two path around the first turn, chased the frontrunners between horses up the backstretch, navigated the second bend from the three path and kept on to the wire. IN HONOR OF ARTIE trailed the field from the two path through the opening half mile, came around the far bend in the three path and improved position in the lane. AWKWARD PAUSE saved ground around the first turn, raced off the pace on the inside up the backstretch, continued to save ground around the far turn and never threatened. MIDNIGHT TEQUILA raced inside in the middle of the pack around the first turn and up the backstretch, navigated the second turn from the two path and was outkicked. PUTMAN raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the second bend still in the three path and made no bid. AIDINGANDABETTING led the field while saving ground around the first turn and up the backstretch, dueled from the rail around the far turn, bumped with MISTA DONZELLA coming off the turn and tired from there. THE RIDER OF HORSE SIX, CHINA BEACH, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE EIGHT, MISTA DONZELLA, CITING INTERFERENCE AT THE QUARTER POLE. UPON REVIEW, NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: TAMPA BAY DOWNS RACE 9 1M Turf CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 15000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Not Started For Less Than $16,000. The Same Preference Will Be Given To Horses Which Have Started For Less Than $16,000 And Since Then Hav e Finished 2nd Or 3rd For $16,000 Or More.). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and Forty Yards.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: THIRD MOON raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend, launched a bid passing the quarter pole and got up for the win late. ROLLERCOASTER MAN raced in the five path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch in the middle of the pack on the outside, began a bid from the two path coming around the far turn, kicked clear entering the stretch and was caught near the wire. STREET COP OFFICER raced off the pace on the inside through the opening half mile, began a bid coming around the second turn, entered the stretch in the six path, drifted in and bumped with PRALINE'S CAT near the sixteenth pole and gained ground late from there. SICILIANO raced in the two path around the first turn, tracked the leader on the inside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the four path, improved position in the lane, bumped with PRALINE'S CAT near the sixteenth pole and continued to gain to the wire. PRALINE'S CAT raced in the three path early, chased the leader between horses up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the five path, gained ground in the lane, bumped with STREET COP OFFICER near the sixteenth pole when that rival drifted in, was forced to take up sharply and finished evenly from there. DENYING trailed the field on the outside through the opening half mile, swung out to the six path for the run around the second bend and passed tiring horses in the lane. DAD'S ON A ROLL raced in the two path around the first turn, led the field on the inside up the backstretch, dueled from the two path around the far bend and weakened in the final furlong. MY EAGLE SOARS raced in the four path around the first turn, stalked the leaders on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the two path and faded in the stretch. FISHERMAN OSCAR hopped up leaving the gate, pressed the pace from the three path through the opening half mile, came around the far turn in the two and three path and tired from there. EL BURRITO raced in the three path around the first turn, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the six path and made no bid. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE INCIDENT NEAR THE SIXTEENTH POLE. ADDITIONALLY, THE RIDER OF HORSE FIVE, PRALINE'S CAT, FILED AN OBJECTION AGAINST HORSE ONE, STREET COP OFFICER, CITING INTERFERENCE IN THAT SAME AREA. UPON REVIEW, HORSE ONE, STREET COP OFFICER, WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR INTERFERENCE AND PLACED FIFTH.
